dataIdInfo.idAbs: This point data layer represents addresses for Manitowoc County, Wisconsin in 2012. [The address point data set contains the situs or physical address locations in Manitowoc County, Wisconsin. The file was created by geocoding the addresses in a telephone directory database against a road centerline file containing address ranges. The mapped points where then moved on top of their corresponding buildings using digital orthophotography as a basemap. Manitowoc County does not issue addresses, but relies on information supplied by the thirty municipalities located in the county to keep the data set current.]
dataIdInfo.idPurp:
This layer is intended for reference and mapping purposes, and may be used for basic applications such as viewing, querying, and map output production, or to provide a basemap to support graphical overlays and analysis with other spatial data.
[The address point data set was originally created for the Manitowoc County Joint Dispatch Center to be used for computer-aided dispatching. It is now used by multiple county departments who need a mapped location of addresses.]

prcStep.stepDesc:
Exported original feature class into a new file geodatabase to maintain the original file format of the data and to conform to UW-Madison's data distribution plan.
[Address points were created by geocoding an AT&T telephone database in 2008. Each point was moved to the main structure identified on Manitowoc County's 2005 digital orthophotograph. Missing points were added using information joined to the tax parcels. Edits are made within days of new information being reported to the GIS Office.]
